modules.description: This module enables incremental JSON construction through a stateful encoder interface, supporting stepwise assembly of nested structures like objects and arrays via start/finish markers. It manages encoding state through an environment type that wraps a Jsonm encoder, allowing partial outputs to be buffered while processing heterogeneous values such as primitives, lists, and nullable fields. Typical applications include generating large JSON documents from streaming data sources or building complex hierarchical responses in memory-efficient web services.

This module provides a stateful interface for incrementally constructing JSON values, allowing nested structures like objects and arrays to be built step by step using start and finish markers. It maintains encoding state through an environment type that wraps a Jsonm encoder, supporting efficient handling of heterogeneous data such as primitives, lists, and nullable fields. Users can assemble large JSON documents from streaming sources or construct complex hierarchical responses in memory-constrained environments. Example uses include generating JSON payloads for web APIs from incremental data or encoding deeply nested configurations with mixed value types.
